            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A planetary mantle is a planetary layer which is an interior part of a terrestrial planet or other rocky body large enough to have differentiation by density.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasBroadSynonym>mantle</oboInOwl:hasBroadSynonym>
        <rdfs:comment>This class is meant to be applicable accross planets. Earth&apos;s mantle would be an instance.</rdfs:comment>
